PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Lambda Z Time Upper Limit

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Lambda Z Time Upper Limit
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The upper limit on time for values to be included in the calculation of Lambda z.

Concepts.definition: The upper limit on timing values to be included in the calculation of Lambda z.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The upper limit on time for values to be included in the calculation of Lambda z, calculated within a dosing interval.

Concepts.definition: The upper limit on time for values to be included in the calculation of Lambda z, calculated within a dosing interval.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Last Measurable Observed Excretion Rate

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Last Measurable Observed Excretion Rate
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate determined for the specimen type specified in PPSPEC.

Concepts.definition: The last measurable (positive) rate.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.definition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the body mass index.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Last Measurable Excretion Rate Normalized by Dose
Concepts.definition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the dose.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Last Measurable Excretion Rate Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Last Measurable Excretion Rate Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Last Measurable Excretion Rate Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The last measurable (positive) excretion rate divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Last Concentration

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Last Concentration
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast.

Concepts.longName: Last Concentration
Concepts.definition: The final measured concentration of a compound in a substance. In pharmacokinetics, it is the concentration corresponding to Tlast.

Concepts.longName: Last Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the body mass index.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Last Concentration Normalized by Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Last Concentration Normalized by Dose
Concepts.definition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the dose.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Last Concentration Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Last Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Last Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Last Concentration Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Last Concentration Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Last Concentration Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The concentration corresponding to Tlast divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cmax

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cmax
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax.

Concepts.longName: Cmax
Concepts.definition: This is a measurement that quantifies the maximum concentration of an experimental substance or drug in the plasma or a target organ after dose administration.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Concentration Dose Normalized

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Concentration Dose Normalized
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Concentration Dose Normalized
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed concentration divided by dose.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Concentration Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The maximum concentration occurring at Tmax, divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Concentration of Unbound Drug

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Concentration of Unbound Drug
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration represented by the unbound fraction of drug, occurring at Tmax.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Concentration of Unbound Drug
Concepts.definition: The maximum concentration represented by the unbound fraction of drug, occurring at Tmax. (CDISC)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum excretion rate determined for the specimen type specified in PPSPEC.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed excretion rate.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum excretion rate divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed excretion rate divided by the body mass index.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum excretion rate divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Dose
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed excretion rate divided by the dose.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum excretion rate divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed excretion rate divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum excretion rate divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Maximum Observed Excretion Rate Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The maximum observed excretion rate divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Mean Absorption Time

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mean Absorption Time
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Mean absorption time of a substance administered by extravascular dosing.

Concepts.longName: Mean Absorption Time
Concepts.definition: The average time that it takes an exogenous compound to enter the circulation.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Collection Interval Midpoint

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Collection Interval Midpoint
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The midpoint of collection interval associated with last measurable excretion rate.

Concepts.longName: Collection Interval Midpoint
Concepts.definition: The midpoint of collection interval, which is associated with last measureable rate.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Time of Maximum Observed Excretion Rate

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Time of Maximum Observed Excretion Rate
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The midpoint of collection interval associated with the maximum excretion rate.

Concepts.longName: Time of Maximum Observed Excretion Rate
Concepts.definition: TThe midpoint of a collection interval associated with the maximum observed excretion rate.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cmin

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cmin
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin).

Concepts.longName: Cmin
Concepts.definition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin).

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Dose

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Dose
Concepts.definition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the dose.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Minimum Concentration Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The minimum concentration between dose time and dose time plus Tau (at Tmin) divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Mean Residence Time Infinity Observed by Extravascular Dose

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mean Residence Time Infinity Observed by Extravascular Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT).

Concepts.longName: Mean Residence Time Infinity Observed by Extravascular Dose
Concepts.definition: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Mean Residence Time Infinity Predicted by Extravascular Dose

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mean Residence Time Infinity Predicted by Extravascular Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT).

Concepts.longName: Mean Residence Time Infinity Predicted by Extravascular Dose
Concepts.definition: The mean residence time (MRT) extrapolated to infinity for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Mean Residence Time to Last Nonzero Concentration by Extravascular Dose

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Mean Residence Time to Last Nonzero Concentration by Extravascular Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Mean residence time (MRT) from the time of dosing to the time of the last measurable concentration for a substance administered by extravascular dosing. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT).

Concepts.longName: Mean Residence Time to Last Nonzero Concentration by Extravascular Dose
Concepts.definition: Mean residence time (MRT) from the time of dosing to the time of the last measurable concentration for a substance administered by extravascular dosing. Extravascular MRT includes Mean Absorption Time (MAT). (CDISC)

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Nonrenal Clearance

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Nonrenal Clearance
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood less the renal clearance.

Concepts.longName: Nonrenal Clearance
Concepts.definition: A measurement of the total clearance rate of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance rate of that substance.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by BMI

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by BMI
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by BMI
Concepts.definition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by Dose

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by Dose
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the dose.

Concepts.longName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by Dose
Concepts.definition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the dose.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by SA

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by SA
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by SA
Concepts.definition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by WT

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by WT
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Nonrenal Clearance Normalized by WT
Concepts.definition: The total clearance of a substance from the blood minus the renal clearance divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Sum of Lambda Z Timepoints

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Sum of Lambda Z Timepoints
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The number of time points used in computing Lambda z.

Concepts.longName: Sum of Lambda Z Timepoints
Concepts.definition: The number of time points used in computing Lambda z.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Number of Points for Lambda z TAU

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Number of Points for Lambda z TAU
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The number of time points used in computing Lambda z determined in a dosing interval.

Concepts.longName: Number of Points for Lambda z TAU
Concepts.definition: The number of time points used in computing Lambda z determined in a dosing interval.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2 divided by body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2 divided by body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Surface Area

Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2 divided by surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2 divided by weight.

Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, over the interval between T1 and T2 divided by weight.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Body Mass Index

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the surface area.

Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Observed Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the weight.

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the surface area.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the weight.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Infinity Predicted Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the recovered administered dose extrapolated to infinity, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU).

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU).

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Body Mass Index

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Body Mass Index
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by the body mass index.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Body Mass Index
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by the body mass index.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Surface Area

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Surface Area
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by surface area.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Surface Area
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by surface area.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Weight

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Weight
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by weight.

Concepts.longName: Percent Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Weight
Concepts.definition: The percentage of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC, between doses (TAU) divided by weight.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Peak Trough Ratio

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Peak Trough Ratio
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The maximum concentration during a dosing interval divided by the concentration at the end of the dosing interval.

Concepts.longName: Peak Trough Ratio
Concepts.definition: The ratio of Cmax to Ctrough during a dosing interval.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: R Squared

ValueMeaning.preferredName: R Squared
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The goodness of fit statistic for the terminal elimination phase.

Concepts.longName: R Squared
Concepts.definition: The goodness of fit statistic for the terminal elimination phase.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Adjusted R Squared

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Adjusted R Squared
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The goodness of fit statistic for the terminal elimination phase, adjusted for the number of time points used in the estimation of Lambda z.

Concepts.longName: Adjusted R Squared
Concepts.definition: The goodness of fit statistic for the terminal elimination phase, adjusted for the number of time points used in the estimation of Lambda z.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Area Under the Curve Ratio

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Area Under the Curve Ratio
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The ratio of two AUC values.

Concepts.longName: Area Under the Curve Ratio
Concepts.definition: The determination of the ratio of one AUC value compared to another AUC value. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Observed

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Observed
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The ratio of two AUC infinity observed values.

Concepts.longName: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Observed
Concepts.definition: The ratio of two AUC infinity observed values.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Predicted

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Predicted
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The ratio of two AUC infinity predicted values.

Concepts.longName: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Predicted
Concepts.definition: The ratio of two AUC infinity predicted values.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cmax to Cmax Ratio Measurement

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cmax to Cmax Ratio Measurement
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The ratio of two Cmax values.

Concepts.longName: Cmax to Cmax Ratio Measurement
Concepts.definition: The determination of the ratio of one Cmax value compared to another Cmax value. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Cmax to Cmin Ratio Measurement

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Cmax to Cmin Ratio Measurement
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The ratio of Cmax value to Cmin value.

Concepts.longName: Cmax to Cmin Ratio Measurement
Concepts.definition: The determination of the ratio of one Cmax value compared to a Cmin value. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Relative Bioavailability

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Relative Bioavailability
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The fraction of the treatment dose that reaches the systemic circulation relative to a reference route or reference formulation. The ratio of the amount of drug in the system (area under the curve) after extravascular or IV administration of a test formulation divided by the drug in the system after extravascular or IV administration of a reference formulation.

Concepts.longName: Relative Bioavailability
Concepts.definition: The ratio of the amount of drug in the system after administration of a test formulation divided by the drug in the system after reference formulation.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Renal Clearance

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Renal Clearance
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The rate at which a substance is removed from the blood via the kidneys.

Concepts.longName: Renal Clearance
Concepts.definition: The rate at which a substance is removed from the blood via the kidneys.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Oral Dosing

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Oral Dosing
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The portion of total clearance attributed to the kidneys expressed as a percentage, following extravascular administration.

Concepts.longName: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Oral Dosing
Concepts.definition: The portion of total clearance attributed to the kidneys expressed as a percentage, following an oral dosing.

PermissibleValues.valueDescription: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Intravenous Dosing

ValueMeaning.preferredName: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Intravenous Dosing
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The portion of total clearance attributed to the kidneys expressed as a percentage, following intravenous administration.

Concepts.longName: Renal Clearance to Total Clearance Ratio Measurement After Intravenous Dosing
